explanation:
## Why Asked
Tests need realistic data without hitting real APIs. Fixtures provide consistent, reusable mock data for component testing scenarios.

## Key Concepts
- Fixture files in cypress/fixtures folder
- cy.fixture() command for loading data
- Passing fixture data as component props
- Separation of test data from test logic

## Code Example
```
// cypress/fixtures/user.json
{"name": "John", "email": "john@example.com"}

// cypress/component/UserCard.cy.ts
import { mount } from 'cypress/react'
import UserCard from './UserCard'

describe('UserCard', () => {
  it('displays user info', () => {
    cy.fixture('user').then(user => {
      mount(<UserCard user={user} />)
      cy.contains('John').should('be.visible')
      cy.contains('john@example.com').should('be.visible')
    })
  })
})
```

